The psychology of auctioning in excess: why spend more money?
To auctions buyers are likely to spend more, to overestimate the goods.
Neurologists and researchers at the University of New York have succeeded in discovering the neuro-economic bases of this known and apparently irrational behavior.
According to their study in Science magazine, men do not want to stay back in a race such as the eBay auction, so they are available to pay even a higher price.
Research has tried to trace the nervous scheme of this "game" at the level of the nervous system through experimental auctions.
One group of volunteers played in the lot, the other group of players participated in a auction while using the functional magnetic resonance imaging method (fMRI) they examined the active areas of the brain of the people participating in the experiment.
In both games the participants could win money, but in the auction game, in which the substantial element is to bid more than the other, the body slammed under the cerebral cortex enters intensively into function when you lose the game.
This brain area, in addition to other functions, plays a role in the "autogratification" mechanism of the nervous system.
Therefore, according to researchers, the price raise is explained by scanning the vehemently reaction of the strata body.
To support their theory, the economists of the research group conducted a financial follow-up investigation.
In this investigation three groups have tendered against a partner under different conditions.
They reported to the control group how much the actual value of the product in question was and they made their bet.
To another group besides that they promised that in the case of winning they would receive another prize of $15.
The third group would have received $15 before auction, but the group members would have lost their money in case of auction loss.
The difference between the two groups consisted of the fact that for one of them the win was emphasized, while for the other, the loss.
By testing the hypothesis of neurologists, the members of the group who played "against loss" were willing to make higher bets than the control group or "winner".
"These results are not deductible from any of the previously existing economic theories.
These so far explained the phenomena found at auctions with the joy of winning and avoiding risk.
Only the methods of creating the neurological image have helped to resolve the contradiction between the two theories, so that we have come to a third explanation," said Andrew Schotter, professor of the Faculty of Economics at the University of New York.
Hepatitis: when to talk to your doctor?
Almost half a billion people in the world suffer from chronic hepatitis B or C, but among the first causes of death, chronic liver disease is mentioned in Hungary.
In Hungary the number of hepatitis patients is 100 thousand, of which only 7000 are cared for: the reason is that many patients do not know how to be infected.
Hepatitis definition is the collective name of the contagious liver disease caused by several viruses.
There are many similarities between symptoms, typical are hepatitis and iteritis, but their pathogens and the diseases caused differ from one another.
Hepatitis viruses spread in two main forms depending on the pathogen: hepatitis A and E through the food channel (e.g. water and infected foods), hepatitis B, C, D and other blood viruses and organic fluids (sperm, vaginal loss, saliva).
For travellers, vaccination against virus A and B is useful, and against C there is no vaccine.
The symptoms of hepatitis A appear two-three weeks after the consumption of infected foods, accompanied by general malaise, weakness, abdominal pain and nausea.
After yellow spots are formed on the skin and on the white of the eyes, the faeces become clear and dark urine, healing occurs within two-three weeks.
One million people die each year worldwide for hepatitis B, the most serious variant of the disease, which causes liver tumors and liver cirrhosis.
The main reason is, according to estimates, that only one person in ten receives pharmacological treatment.
Hepatitis C can also have very serious consequences: if not treated it can cause liver cirrhosis and liver tumors.
Most infected people do not know that they have contracted the disease because pathogens subdulge the liver cells, in many cases the first symptoms appear after 20-30 years.
Therefore it is very important to prevent and carry out regular medical analyses.
This disease is much more frequent than the average in three groups: those who had a blood transfusion before 1991, drug addicts and tattoos.
In the world today the number of people infected with chronic hepatitis C virus amounts to 200 million.
Since a routine laboratory test also reveals the disease, it is worth addressing your family doctor when you notice any symptoms of unknown origin.
Recognized in time the disease is curable, the virus can be eliminated by the body, so the infectious power ceases and the formation of tumors can be prevented.
September 30 is the world day of hepatitis, organized for the first time in 2004 worldwide by associations of patients.
The aim is to draw attention to chronic viral hepatitis, the causes of its development and the early recognition of the disease.
Who believes in God feels less pain?
According to the result of a recent investigation religious faith works as a kind of analgesic that has made the death of Catholic martyrs more bearable.
The scientists at Oxford University conducted an interesting experiment, examining how faith in God affects the feeling of pain, the British Telegraph reported.
In the context of the somewhat bizarre investigation, an electroshock was carried out to 12 Catholic believers and to the same atheists, while all observed a painting depicting the Virgin Mary.
Based on the results, Catholic believers were able to reject much of the pain.
Thanks to the exploratory technique of the human brain it was discovered that Catholics were able to activate the part of the brain responsible for pain control.
The test is the first of a series of research in which scientists, philosophers and theologians from the University are also involved.
The test was exactly like this: an instrument that emits discharges and passes the electroshock was connected to the left hand of the subject of the experiment.
The researchers asked the participants to focus on two paintings, the virgin Mary painted in the seventeenth century by Sassoferrato and the Lady with the hermelin by Leonardo da Vinci painted in the fifteenth century.
The authors of the examination hoped that the image of the virgin Mary would give rise to a kind of religious state among believers, while Leonardo's picture was chosen because it did not differ too much from the other and felt it had peaceful effect.
Subjects of the experiment spent half an hour in front of the MRI scanner and in this time ring received 20 electroshocks in four consecutive series, while observing either the religious or other painting.
Catholics reported that the vision of the virgin Mary made them feel "safe", as if "someone took care of them" and "they calmed down and were permeated by peace".
Looking at the religious theme image they realized 12% less pain than when they had before them the work of Leonardo.
The psychologist Miguel Farias, who took part in the test himself, believes that such a result can be achieved with any image with a strong effect even for atheists, however, you need to find the right image.
"We must look for an image to which they have very positive feelings, like a mother or a father," said the psychologist.
The Anglican bishop Tom Wright welcomed the result of the search.
"The practice of faith should change, and in many cases it can change our personality." - added Wright.
After the excellent results, only the question remains if the painting of a Madonna by Leonardo or another painter of such caliber is presented to believers, what effect could it have on the control of pain?
Would the vision of a quality virgin Mary bring better results?
