As a result of the change in domestic and export prices, industrial production costs were higher than 0.7% compared to the previous month and 3.2% compared to one year ago.
The prices of the previous month's domestic industrial sales rose only by 0.1%.
National sales prices in the manufacturing sector also rose to a minimum of 0.1%, compared to July.
The increase in prices in August 2008 took place in the field of leather and shoes processing (2.8%), especially bags and belts with 4.6% and production of shoes with 2.5% monthly increase.
The high price level of plastic and chemical raw materials has resulted in a significant monthly increase (1.6%) in the chemicals and products sector.
A decrease in prices occurred in the oil processing sector (1.4%), in the production of electrical instruments and machinery (0.9%) and to a minimum extent in the processing of wood (0.1%)
The prices of paper production, editorial and typographical activities have not changed.
In the other sectors of the manufacturing industry there has been an increase in prices between 0.2 and 0.9%.
